originalText.text: My wife and I visited this congregation in February 2016 while on our 15th anniversary trip to NYC. Very sweet family of faith. Worship was encouraging and uplifting. Everyone was friendly. We even stayed and had extended fellowship with them. I highly recommend this assembly to any living in or visiting New York City.

originalText.text: Was visiting my folks in NYC and wanted to attend a service. The service was orderly yet spirit filled. Worship was inspirational and the word was fundamental. It was one of the most welcoming places or worship I've been to. The congregation is diverse and I really spending the Sabbath with Shaar Adonai. I will be attending when I'm in the City again. Lord willing.

originalText.text: I heard a wonderful testamonial from the Rabbi at this congregation and I was interested to take the chance an begin to look into a new possible messianic congregation for myself.  The members were welcoming, but unfortunately the Rabbi's wife was extremely abrupt and unwelcoming. Fortunality, Yeshua stirred me in the right direction.
